caption: So many places to visit in Paris, you walk, you walk, and you walk more. Especially in the quarter of Le Marais. So you walk to La Place des Vosges and here it comes, on your way you realize that you are exhausted. And suddenly, again, in front of you a small square and its benches, its flowers and its beautiful sculpture. This is the ideal place for a break, for a repleneshing pause to refill your batteries.
I love that beauty is free in Paris and it certainly resides in this small square!!!!  Beautiful statues, scented by roses and those who know this little secret tucked away in the Marais!
A perfect place for a picnic, plenty of seating, lush leafy shade, and lots sculptures and stone art to appreciate.
